Most of the time, opposite Drury, Opener will bid game directly 
or sign off in 2M = no interest in game over here.
If he's not sure he can bid a new suit as a Help Suit Game Try 
keeping in mind that we're not looking for another trump suit as we've already found our Major fit.|pg||at|

One extra little trick available: After 
Pass  Pass   1M   Pass 
2@c               Pard with a full opener but not sure about game, can rebid 2@d  (artificial = alert) 
                    to say "How good is your hand for Drury? 
                    Do you have a good side suit for tricks? and so on. 
Responder can go back to 2 of the Major with a minimum and no good suit to show.
We'll see lots of these in todays deals|pg||at|

Questions? 
Kibby: What constitutes a good suit?
T: Good suit = KQJx or AKxx, something that'll produce ready tricks
@sKxxx @hKQJx @dQx @cxxx   is better than   @sKJxx @hKx @dQxx @cQxxx 
even though the HCP are the same.

Kibby: Any advantage to reverse drury or 2-way drury?
T: The 2-way simply means: one shows 3-card support and the other 4 and I think that's a huge help.
"Reverse Drury" simply means: going back to 2M is a weak bid, 
while anything else is forward going.
In original Drury  1M - 2@c - 2@d  was weak and anything else was forward going 
- those meanings have been reversed:
The 2@d rebid as a positive hand leaves more room for Responder to show good holdings. 
The only change in thinking is that 2@c or 2@d by a passed hand over 1M can't be used to show clubs or diamonds,
but, hey, who cares about minors?


